cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a control design approach for a Learning Model Predictive Controller (LMPC) for iterative tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The LMPC is reference-free and improves its performance by learning from previous iterations, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The LMPC uses a safe set and a terminal cost function to guarantee recursive feasibility and non-increasing performance, which involves AI techniques. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The LMPC can be applied to control robots performing iterative tasks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to the implementation of the LMPC.
